meta.methodology: Composite US Influence Index v1.1 (0-100). Formula: score = clamp[0,100](12 + 0.10*allied_institutions_exposure + 0.12*fdi_from_us + 0.14*trade_with_us_pct + 0.30*security_ties + 0.12*tech_dependency + 0.17*financial_exposure + 0.05*logistics_exposure). Inputs are pre-normalized 0-100 indicators; stored numeric output is rounded to one decimal precision (whole-number values may appear without trailing .0 in JSON serialization). This revision raises baseline structural influence and increases weights for security_ties and financial_exposure to better reflect current geopolitical conditions.
sources: IMF IMTS (International Trade in Goods by partner, formerly DOTS)
IMF COFER (Currency Composition of Official Foreign Exchange Reserves, aggregate context)
UN Comtrade bilateral trade + HS 8542 (semiconductors) / HS 8517 (telecom equipment)
UNCTAD bilateral FDI matrices (inward FDI stock/flow from US)
World Bank Projects & Operations API (country-level engagement)
DoD Base Structure Report / Military Bases geospatial dataset
US Treasury TIC (Treasury International Capital) releases
IEA EV/battery supply-chain data (tech dependence proxy)
USGS Mineral Commodity Summaries (strategic minerals proxy)
assumptions: Security ties scored via NATO membership (70-95), treaty alliances (70-90), MNNA status (55-75), bilateral defense agreements (30-55), no formal ties (3-25)
Trade percentage based on IMF IMTS bilateral goods trade as share of reporter total trade
FDI from US normalized as share of total inward FDI stock using UNCTAD data
Tech dependency proxied via HS 8542/8517 import share from US + US cloud/platform adoption indices
Financial exposure captures USD denomination of trade/debt, SWIFT usage, and TIC-reported holdings
Logistics exposure reflects proximity to US military basing nodes and reliance on US-secured sea lanes
Allied institutions exposure measures World Bank/IMF program engagement and UN voting alignment with US
